cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on improving the throughput of content-centric wireless networks through pushing and caching techniques. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a Joint Pushing and Caching (JPC) method that involves determining the contents to be pushed and removed from the receiver buffer in each timeslot, which involves algorithmic design and analysis. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the statistical and causal content Request Delay Information (RDI) used in the JPC policies, which involves information theory concepts. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes online JPC policies that use causal feedback of user requests to enhance performance, which involves control system design. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with content-centric wireless networks, which involve multimedia content delivery.
